Codables:
Codable isn’t a protocol on it’s own, but an alias for two other protocols: Encodable and Decodable. As you might guess, those two protocols declare that types can be encoded to and decoded from a different format.
struct Toy: Codable {
}
struct Employee: Codable {
}
In ablove examples all the stored properties of Employee and Toy will be codables by default and Many basic types in the Swift Standard Library and Foundation types (for example, String and URL) are codable.
Note: You can encode codable types to various formats such as Property Lists (PLists), XML or JSON











